JOHANNESBURG Metal workers union, Numsa has weighed in on the Cabinet reshuffle, which it believes is the result of a clash between white and black capitalist classes.The union says greedy capitalists are battling each other for control over the government and its budget.Numsa says it expects the crisis to worsen in coming months.READ: Numsa workers go on strike at Road Accident FundIt s also denounced the country's recent credit downgrade saying ratings agencies shouldn't be taken seriously.Numsa lists a national living wage among a host of demands and warned of potential mass action in the near future.eNCA